Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Trim the @green beans{80%g} and chop into thirds. Halve the @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} widthways. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop the @salted peanuts{25%g}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

When the oil is hot, add the @British pork mince{240%g}. Season with @salt and @ground black pepper{} and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, add the green beans and broccoli to the pan of boiling water.

Bring back up to the boil, then add the @egg noodle nest{2}. Simmer until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}.

> TIP: Run the noodles and veg under cold water to stop the noodles sticking together and to keep the veg vibrant.

Once the pork mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Add the onion to the pan and stir together.

Cook until the onion is golden, ~{4-5%minutes} then stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @water{75%ml} for the sauce, @bulgogi sauce{150%ml} and @soy sauce{}. Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly reduced, ~{30%seconds}.

Add the noodles and veg to the pan with the pork.

Toss to coat and add a splash of water if you feel it needs it, then heat through until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Taste and add salt and pepper if needed.

When everything is ready, serve your bulgogi pork noodles in #bowls{}.

Sprinkle the peanuts on top and @?red chilli flakes{1%tsp}. Enjoy!